# Test Analysis: inventory_manager

## Source: inventory_manager.h.spec.md
## Report: test_suite_inventory_inventory_manager.c.report

---

## 1. Failing Tests Summary

| Line | Assertion | Failure Description |
|------|-----------|---------------------|
| 33   | `p_found != NULL` | `get_inventory_by__uuid_in__inventory_manager` returned null after allocation |
| 78   | `p_found_a != NULL` | Same lookup failure in a multi-allocation scenario |
| 109  | `p_found != NULL` | Same lookup failure after allocation |

All three failures share the same pattern: an inventory is allocated via
`allocate_p_inventory_using__this_uuid_in__inventory_manager`, then a lookup
via `get_inventory_by__uuid_in__inventory_manager` returns null when it should
return the allocated inventory.

